Polymetal Declines Most in 2 Weeks as Silver Price Retreats

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-05-23T15:12:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/polymetal-declines-most-in-week-as-silver-price-retreats.html
OAO Polymetal, a Russian silver
producer, slid the most in almost two weeks as the price of the
metal dropped.  The shares fell 3.8 percent to 476.4 rubles by the 6:45
p.m. close in Moscow, their biggest loss since May 12.  Silver for immediate delivery declined as much as 1.3
percent to $34.615 an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
